== Why Robotics Matters

Robotics is an important subject because it helps you understand how technology and engineering come together in real life.

When you learn robotics, you also learn how to think like a problem solver.

It helps you develop:
- Logical thinking and reasoning  
- Creativity and curiosity  
- Understanding of machines and systems  
- Teamwork and structured thinking  

